snippet.textDisplay: Watching the highlights I can believe how many back foot no balls the umpires are missing!! Stokes especially bowling round the wicket. Seems to be a common umpiring trend now in in the modern game, that no balls are only ever questioned when there is doubt that a wicket is taken? Surely if bowling is now too quick for the umpires to see the delivery stride no ball, then technology should be used as it is in tennis? or maybe get better umpires?
